Naledi Shange, News24ER24 (Picture: Supplied) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg - An act of bravery ended in double tragedy in Randburg, Johannesburg, on Tuesday when a six-year-old boy and a man drowned in a swimming pool at the boy's house.&nbsp;ER24 paramedics said a bystander informed them that the child had been playing outside when he a fell into the pool.&nbsp;The man, who was working at the house, jumped in and tried to save the child, said ER24 spokesperson Pieter Rossouw.&nbsp;"He could not swim and became unconscious in the water," he said.&nbsp;He was declared dead on the scene.&nbsp;The child was transported privately to Mediclinic Sandton, but was also declared dead on arrival at the hospital.Rossouw called on people to be cautious around pools and said&nbsp;children should never be left unattended near water.&nbsp;"You should never jump in after someone who might be drowning. Rather use a rope, stick or [floating] device to help," he said.&nbsp;24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.